main_5830733\" data-toggle=\"modal\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Jan 18, 2024</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104rgw1705580165965_2.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/rgw1705580165965_2.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/rgw1705580165965_2.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"tit1665702618427\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n                     \n Define Keyboard Shortcuts for Menu Items\n   </h1>\n<div class=\"body taskbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">Menu definitions can define keyboard shortcuts that enable the user to select a menu item using the keyboard rather than the mouse. Keyboard shortcuts can be defined as an <dfn class=\"term\">access key</dfn> or an <dfn class=\"term\">accelerator key</dfn>.\n </p>\n<section class=\"section context\" id=\"tit1665702618427__context_w3860ab1b5b1_w3861ab1b5_w3862ab1\">\n<div class=\"div context\" id=\"tit1665702618427__topic_d26624e1_d26625e1_d26626e1\">\n<ul class=\"ul\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"tit1665702618427__li_d13388e1_d13389e1_d13390e1\">Access key—a letter in a menu name, such as\n                     <span class=\"ph gold\">F</span> in the <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">File</span> menu. <p class=\"p\" id=\"tit1665702618427__p_d26627e1_d26628e1_d26629e1\">By default, the first letter in a menu option\n                     is the access key. If that letter has already been used by a previous menu\n                     item, a different letter is automatically used.</p> To define a different\n                  access key edit the menu option <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Title</span> and place a percent\n                  sign (<code class=\"ph codeph\">%</code>) before the character to use as the access key. </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"tit1665702618427__li_d13391e1_d13392e1_d13393e1\">Accelerator key—a key combination, such as <code class=\"ph codeph\">Alt+O</code> to open a file. The key combination is displayed next to the menu item.\n </li>\n</ul>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"tit1665702618427__p_d26633e1_d26634e1_d26635e1\">To define an accelerator key:</p>\n</div>\n</section>\n<section><ol class=\"ol steps\"><li class=\"li step stepexpand\" id=\"tit1665702618427__li_d13394e1_d13395e1_d13396e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\">In the <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Accelerator</span> property of the menu item, enter a logical name for the menu sequence or action, such as <code class=\"ph codeph\">FileOpen</code>.\n </span>\n<div class=\"itemgroup info\">\n<div class=\"note note note_note\" id=\"tit1665702618427__note_w3863ab1b5b3b1b3b1_w3864ab1b5b3b1b3_w3865ab1b5b3b1_w3866ab1b5b3_w3867ab1b5_w3868ab1\"><span class=\"note__title\">Note:</span> The maximum length of a logical name is 30 characters.</div>\n</div>\n</li><li class=\"li step stepexpand\" id=\"tit1665702618427__li_d13397e1_d13398e1_d13399e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\" id=\"tit1665702618427__p_d26636e1_d26637e1_d26638e1\">In the [accelerators] section of the\n               application's <span class=\"ph filepath\">.ini</span> file, assign the desired keyboard sequence to\n               this logical name.</span>\n<div class=\"itemgroup info\">For example, <code class=\"ph codeph\">FileOpen=Alt+O</code></div>\n</li></ol></section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div><div class=\"contentPlaceholder\" style=\"height: 500px;\"><div class=\"contentContainer zDocsSideBoxes\"><div><h5 aria-level=\"5\" class=\"css-g931ng\">Related Links</h5><ul><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/fuu1665702671109.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>[accelerators]</a><p>The [accelerators] section of the initialization file enables you to map a logical function, such as fileopen to a keyboard sequence (an accelerator) such as Ctrl+F7.</p></li></ul></div></div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_5830733\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_5830733\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Define Keyboard Shortcuts for Menu Items Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Jan 18, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Define Keyboard Shortcuts for Menu Items Menu definitions can define keyboard shortcuts that enable the user to select a menu item using the keyboard rather than the mouse. Keyboard shortcuts can be defined as an access key or an accelerator key . Access key—a letter in a menu name, such as F in the File menu. By default, the first letter in a menu option is the access key. If that letter has already been used by a previous menu item, a different letter is automatically used. To define a different access key edit the menu option Title and place a percent sign ( % ) before the character to use as the access key. Accelerator key—a key combination, such as Alt+O to open a file. The key combination is displayed next to the menu item. To define an accelerator key: In the Accelerator property of the menu item, enter a logical name for the menu sequence or action, such as FileOpen . Note: The maximum length of a logical name is 30 characters. In the [accelerators] section of the application's .ini file, assign the desired keyboard sequence to this logical name. For example, FileOpen=Alt+O Related Links [accelerators] The [accelerators] section of the initialization file enables you to map a logical function, such as fileopen to a keyboard sequence (an accelerator) such as Ctrl+F7. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}